# Rule: Discuss Planton Catalog System

**Purpose**: Equip an AI agent with complete architectural knowledge of the docs catalog system so it can answer questions, discuss design decisions, plan changes, and reason about the system without needing to re-explore the codebase each time.

**Trigger**: User references this rule, asks about how the catalog system works, wants to discuss design decisions, or is planning changes to the catalog infrastructure.

**Scope boundary**: This rule covers the catalog **system infrastructure** (build pipeline, rendering, configuration). For the content standard of individual catalog pages (what sections they must contain, how to write them), see the rules in `_rules/docs/`:
- `write-planton-component-catalog-page.mdc` -- writing new catalog pages
- `audit-planton-component-catalog-page.mdc` -- auditing existing catalog page content

For hands-on auditing and fixing of the system infrastructure, see the companion rule:
- `site/_rules/audit-and-fix-planton-catalog-system.mdc`

---

## What the Catalog System Is

The catalog system transforms hand-written `catalog-page.md` files co-located with each deployment component into the public documentation site at `/docs/catalog/`. It handles:

- Copying source markdown from the API directory tree to the site's public directory
- Extracting titles from H1 headings and stripping provider prefixes for sidebar labels
- Generating URL-friendly slugs from titles
- Rewriting internal catalog links from directory-name-based paths to slug-based paths
- Generating provider index pages listing all components under each provider
- Copying preset YAML/MD pairs and generating preset list pages
- Generating a JSON structure file that drives the sidebar and catalog grid at runtime

---

## File Map

### Source Files (authored by humans/agents)

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apis/dev/planton/provider/{provider}/{component}/v1/catalog-page.md` | The source catalog page for a component. Hand-written, follows the catalog page standard. Contains an H1 heading with the component's display name (including provider prefix). |
| `apis/dev/planton/provider/{provider}/{component}/v1/docs/README.md` | Legacy research document. Used as fallback when no `catalog-page.md` exists. Being gradually replaced. |
| `apis/dev/planton/provider/{provider}/{component}/v1/presets/*.yaml` | Preset manifest files. Each is a complete, deployable YAML manifest. |
| `apis/dev/planton/provider/{provider}/{component}/v1/presets/*.md` | Preset description files. Each pairs with a YAML file of the same base name. |

### Canonical Provider Definitions

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apis/dev/planton/shared/cloudresourcekind/cloud_resource_provider.proto` | The single source of truth for all provider enum values. Each enum carries a `provider_meta` annotation with `group` (API group domain) and `display_name` (human-readable name). Every provider configuration in the catalog system must trace back to this file. |

### Build Scripts

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/scripts/copy-component-docs.ts` | The main build script. Performs: source scanning, title extraction from H1 headings, provider prefix stripping, slug generation, frontmatter injection, internal link rewriting, preset copying, provider index generation, catalog index generation. Contains `PROVIDER_DISPLAY_NAMES` and `PROVIDER_PREFIXES` configuration maps. |
| `site/scripts/generate-docs-structure.ts` | Post-copy structure generator. Scans the built `site/public/docs/` directory, reads YAML frontmatter from every markdown file, and produces `site/public/docs-structure.json` -- the JSON tree that drives the sidebar and catalog grid at runtime. |

### Intermediate Build Outputs

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/public/docs/catalog/{provider}/{slug}/index.md` | Built component catalog page with injected frontmatter (title, description, icon, order, componentName). |
| `site/public/docs/catalog/{provider}/{slug}/presets/` | Built preset files (YAML, MD with frontmatter, index.md). |
| `site/public/docs/catalog/{provider}/index.md` | Built provider index page listing all components with links. |
| `site/public/docs/catalog/index.md` | Built catalog index page (minimal -- the grid is rendered by React). |
| `site/public/docs-structure.json` | JSON tree of all docs. Drives sidebar and catalog grid. |

### React Components (runtime rendering)

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/src/app/docs/components/DocsSidebar.tsx` | Sidebar. Loads `docs-structure.json`, renders expandable directory tree. For catalog providers, shows `ProviderIcon` + title from structure. For components, shows per-component icon with letter-badge fallback + title from frontmatter. |
| `site/src/app/docs/components/CatalogProviderGrid.tsx` | Catalog index page grid. Renders a 2-column card grid of providers with icon, display title, and component count. Receives data from `extractCatalogProviders()` in the page component. |
| `site/src/app/docs/components/ProviderIcon.tsx` | Provider-level icon. Resolves SVG via `getProviderIconPath()`, falls back to a letter badge showing the first character of the provider name. |
| `site/src/app/docs/utils/providerIcons.ts` | Icon path resolution utility. Convention: `/images/providers/{provider}.svg`. Contains `PROVIDER_ICON_OVERRIDES` map for non-standard filenames (e.g., `atlas` -> `mongodb-atlas.svg`). |
| `site/src/app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` | The main docs page component. Contains `extractCatalogProviders()` which reads provider entries from `docs-structure.json` and passes `name`, `title`, `path`, `componentCount` to the catalog grid. |

