## Configuration Surfaces

These are the places that must be updated when providers or components change:

### When Adding a New Provider

1. `cloud_resource_provider.proto` -- add enum value with `provider_meta`
2. `apis/dev/planton/provider/{newprovider}/` -- create component directories
3. `PROVIDER_DISPLAY_NAMES` in `copy-component-docs.ts` -- add display name entry
4. `PROVIDER_PREFIXES` in `copy-component-docs.ts` -- add prefix stripping entry
5. `PROVIDER_ICON_OVERRIDES` in `providerIcons.ts` -- only if SVG filename is non-standard
6. `site/public/images/providers/{provider}.svg` -- add icon SVG (optional; letter badge fallback works)

### When Adding a New Component

No system changes needed. The build script auto-discovers components by scanning provider directories. Just create the `catalog-page.md` file.

### When Renaming a Provider

Update all four maps in the build script and icon utility, plus rename the directory under `apis/dev/planton/provider/`.

### When Changing a Provider Display Name

Update `PROVIDER_DISPLAY_NAMES` in `copy-component-docs.ts` and rebuild.

---

## Build Pipeline Commands

Run from the `site/` directory, always in this order:

```shell
yarn copy-docs            # Phase 1: copy and transform catalog pages
yarn generate-structure   # Phase 2: generate docs-structure.json from built output
yarn dev                  # Phase 3: start dev server (loads structure at runtime)
```

`copy-docs` must run before `generate-structure` because the structure script reads the frontmatter written by the copy script.

