## Relationship to Other Rules

| Rule | Scope |
|------|-------|
| `_rules/docs/write-planton-component-catalog-page.mdc` | How to **write** the content of a single `catalog-page.md` file (section structure, field reference format, tone, verification protocol) |
| `_rules/docs/audit-planton-component-catalog-page.mdc` | How to **audit** the content of a single `catalog-page.md` file (structural checks, field verification, manifest validation, tone audit) |
| `site/_rules/audit-and-fix-planton-catalog-system.mdc` | How to **audit and fix** the catalog system infrastructure (build pipeline, provider maps, sidebar rendering, slug generation) |
| `site/_rules/discuss-planton-catalog-system.mdc` | **This rule.** Architectural context for discussing the catalog system. |

The content rules (`_rules/docs/`) operate at the individual component level. The system rules (`site/_rules/`) operate at the infrastructure level. A healthy catalog requires both: correct content in each catalog page, and a correctly configured system to build and render those pages.
